Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.

Quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add onion and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @shrimp{10%ounce} and @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water. Pat shrimp or chicken dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or chicken for pork; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, 3-4 minutes for shrimp or 4-6 minutes for chicken.

While pork cooks, in a large #bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the cilantro, juice from half the lime (whole lime for 4 servings), @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Stir @tex-mex paste{1%unit} into pan with pork mixture until fully coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork filling, @monterey jack cheese{¼%cup}, slaw, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.